        <h3>Addendum</h3>
        <p><strong>Problem Solved:</strong> The main objective of this project was to create a job application tracker that allows users to add job applications, set their status (Applied, Interviewing, Offered, or Rejected), and manage them by moving applications between these categories.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Solution Overview:</strong> I implemented a solution using JavaScript to handle form submissions, store each job application in an array, and dynamically display the applications based on their status. The interface updates in real-time as applications are moved between statuses, offering an intuitive way to track job application progress.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Challenges and Solutions:</strong> One challenge I encountered was ensuring that the applications could seamlessly move between different status categories without refreshing the page. I resolved this by utilizing JavaScript functions to filter and update the applications array based on their current status. Styling consistency across dynamic elements was another challenge, which I addressed by carefully applying CSS classes to each interactive element. This approach helped achieve a uniform and visually appealing design.</p>
